-- Merkel Urges Direct Israeli, Palestinian Peace Talks in Abbas Phone Call
-- Patrick Donahue
-- 2010-07-23T14:41:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-23/merkel-urges-direct-israeli-palestinian-peace-talks-in-abbas-phone-call.html

          
          
             Chancellor Angela Merkel called on
Israeli and Palestinian negotiators to enter into direct peace
talks. Merkel spoke today by phone with Palestinian President
Mahmoud Abbas and yesterday with Egyptian President Hosni
Mubarak, the German government said in an e-mailed statement.   
 “In the telephone call it was made clear how important
rapid agreement on a time schedule for the talks is in this
context,” the German government said in the statement today in
Berlin.    
          
          


  


        